Ngl my experience of being autistic feel like a, excuse my language, dogshit fucking nightmare. Such a socially isolating experience that leaves you feel formless and hopeless since all of humanity and being alive is having a social factor

How do you tell your emotionally crippled mother that no, she shouldn't foster children, and first she should spend more time working through her emotions in therapy? I'm just worried they'll also get emotional neglect

Idk if it's because of being autistic but it feels like living my life is a fucking nightmare. I mean, it's probably because of the other mental health issues that compounded throughout my life but then it becomes a question of whether it happened because I was autistic or not
Sometimes we have to ask ourselves if our best option is to just suffer in silence ?
Not gonna lie, I am stuck in the feeling that life with n o t get any better and so I am surrendered to that and kinda defeated lol
